6. Har styremedlemmer krav på å få informasjon om enkeltsaker?
According to the provided document, the law does not give individual board members the right to carry out investigations on their own. Instead, they must make the request to the board, which will then initiate the investigation. However, individual board members are obliged to stay informed and can demand more information if the managing director is not providing sufficient information. Additionally, if the employees need to be informed about certain matters, it is often the responsibility of the managing director or, in some cases, the chairman of the board to disseminate the information. Ultimately, it will depend on the company's policy and the discretion of the board to determine how much and what type of information individual board members are entitled to receive. Therefore, it is not clear if individual board members always have the right to access information on specific matters.

