1. Når har de ansatte rett til å bli representert i styret?
De ansatte har rett til � bli representert i styret i alle selskaper med mer enn 30 eller 50 ansatte, avhengig av om selskapet har en bedriftsforsamling eller ikke, jf. aksjeloven � 6-4. Dette gir de ansatte en demokratisk rett til � delta i beslutninger som ang�r dem selv, og bidrar til �kt verdiskaping ved at de ansattes kompetanse og informasjon om virksomheten tas inn som beslutningsgrunnlag.

2. Må styret opplyse de ansatte om deres rettigheter til å ha ansattevalgt representant?
Yes, the board has an obligation to inform the employees about their right to have employee-elected representatives on the board. This obligation is stated in the representative regulation, which also regulates the election process of these representatives. Additionally, the employees have a democratic right to participate in decisions that affect them, which is facilitated by their representation on the board.

3. Gjelder deltidsansatte som en ansatt i forhold til styrerepresentasjon?
Yes, according to the information provided in the relevant topic data, both full-time and part-time employees are included in the calculation of the number of employees for the purpose of employee representation on the board. A person who works less than 50% of a full-time position is considered a part-time employee and is counted as half an employee in the calculation. Therefore, part-time employees do count as employees in relation to board representation.

4. Kan styret eller aksjonærene bestemme tjenestetiden til et ansattevalgt styremedlem?
No, neither the board nor the shareholders can decide the tenure of an employee-elected board member. The employee-elected board members are elected by the employees and their tenure is regulated by law. The representative regulation specifies the term of office for employee-elected board members, which is two years for companies with more than 30 employees and four years for companies with more than 50 employees. Therefore, the tenure of an employee-elected board member is determined by the rules and regulations governing the election process and not by the board or the shareholders.

5. Er et ansattevalgt styremedlem å regne som et fullverdig styremedlem?
Yes, according to the information provided in the relevant topic data, an employee-elected board member is considered a full-fledged board member who represents the company's overall interests, not just the employees' interests. While the role of an employee-elected board member can be challenging, they are expected to bring the perspective of the employees into the boardroom. Therefore, an employee-elected board member holds the same status as an outside-appointed or shareholder-elected board member.

